The privatisation of sugar companies has reignited boundary wars between Rift Valley and Nyanza counties, the Star has established. It is part of the wider scheme by cartels to maintain a grip on the sector that is controlled by business people. They want both Chemelil and Muhuroni, which are based in Kisumu county, to move to Kericho and Nandi counties. “It is not just privatisation, but we want the issues being raised by all stakeholders to be addressed,” Kisumu governor Anyang Nyong’o said in April.  